# NIOV Labs Foundation -- Cursor Rules
# Cursor reads this before every AI interaction.
## THE MOST IMPORTANT RULE
Claude Code builds sections. Cursor understands and reviews them.
Never do Claude Code job. Never rewrite or restructure code
that Claude Code built unless specifically asked after it finished.
## WHAT CURSOR OWNS
- Answering questions about code in plain English
- Explaining what a function or file does
- Reviewing completed sections for rule violations (read-only by default)
- Surgical single-file fixes when repair agent is stuck (3+ attempts)
- Checking 4-line comments exist on all functions
- Catching missing audit trail writes in data-touching functions
## WHAT CLAUDE CODE OWNS -- CURSOR STAYS OUT
- Building entire sections from the PRD specification
- Running the test suite (npx vitest run)
- Installing npm packages
- Database migrations (npx prisma migrate dev)
- Any change spanning more than 2 files at once
## CURSOR BEHAVIOR RULES
C1 -- EXPLAIN BEFORE YOU CHANGE
Before any edit: CHANGING: [what] BECAUSE: [why]
Show the diff. Wait for approval. Then apply.
C2 -- ONE FILE AT A TIME
Touch exactly one file per fix.
More than one file needed: report MULTI-FILE NEEDED and stop.
# .cursorrules continued -- paste below Part 1
C3 -- NEVER MODIFY TEST FILES
Files in /tests/ are never touched. Fix production code only.
C4 -- NEVER ADD PACKAGES WITHOUT PERMISSION
Report: PACKAGE NEEDED: [name] FOR: [reason]. Wait for yes.
C5 -- COMMENT FORMAT IS MANDATORY
Every function must have this 4-line comment above it:
// WHAT: what this function does
// INPUT: what goes in
// OUTPUT: what comes out
// WHY: why this matters to NIOV Foundation
C6 -- NEVER HARD DELETE
Flag any .delete() or .destroy() on production data.
C7 -- AUDIT TRAIL CHECK
Any function reading or writing a Memory Capsule must write
to the audit trail BEFORE returning. Flag if missing.
C8 -- REPORT FORMAT AFTER ANY CHANGE
CHANGED: [file and what changed]
REASON: [why in plain English]
CLAUDE CODE NEEDED: [yes or no]
## TECH STACK -- NEVER SUGGEST ALTERNATIVES
Backend: Node.js + TypeScript + Fastify
Database: Supabase PostgreSQL + Prisma
Cache: Upstash Redis | Storage: Supabase Storage
Frontend: Next.js | Testing: Vitest